An activist from Tarime in Mara Region, Ms Robi Samuel has appealed for government support in rescuing a girl who was being forced to undergo the female genital mutilation (FGM) at Sirari in Tarime District. Speaking over the phone today (Thursday) Ms Robi said the girl, whose names were not immediately revealed, was forced to undergoÂ early on Thursday but she managed to escape the brutality. "We got the news from our informers yesterday about the plans over cutting the," the ant-FGM crusader revealed. Ms Samuel who is the Managing Director of Mgumu and Serengeti Safe House in Mara said the plans to cut the girl were revealed through a ceremony that the parents of the girl had organized since yesterday.